Travellers desperate to get home are still stuck at the Beitbridge border. Many have been waiting for days to cross over, and one person has died in the long line. eNCA's Siphamandla Goge is live from Musina in Limpopo. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The situation at the Beitbridge Border Post is getting worse. Travellers have been stuck for more than 5 days waiting to get to the other side of Zimbabwe. READ: Woman dies while waiting to cross border to Zimbabwe On Tuesday, a Zimbabwean citizen reportedly died after collapsing near the Beitbridge border in Limpopo. Authorities say it will take some time to clear the situation. For more details on this story, watch the video above.